sections.Biography:
===Background===
Ser Boros is a member of [[House Blount]], a noble house from the [[Crownlands]].

===[[Season 1]]===
Ser Boros was among the guards that attacked [[Eddard Stark]] when he tried to de-throne King Joffrey.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[You Win or You Die]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; He was also present when Ser [[Barristan Selmy]] was dismissed from the Kingsguard.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
[[File:Tyrion speech.jpg|thumb|Tyrion rallying the troops]]
During the [[Battle of the Blackwater]], Ser Boros and Ser [[Mandon Moore]] remain at the side of King [[Joffrey]] as he oversees the [[King's Landing|city]]'s defenses alongside [[Tyrion Lannister]], the [[Hand of the King]]. When Queen [[Cersei Lannister|Cersei]] learns that the forces of [[Stannis Baratheon]] have almost breached the walls, she orders Joffrey to be brought into the safety of the [[Red Keep]]. When told that he has to leave the wall at the behest of Queen Cersei, Joffrey, who has never shown much courage in the face of adversity, complies and orders Ser Mandon and Ser Boros to aid Tyrion and fight on in his stead. They stand behind Tyrion as he gives a speech to rally the troops. &lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Blackwater (episode)|Blackwater]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===
Ser Boros, along with his three sworn brothers, is present at the [[Great Hall (Red Keep)|Great Hall]] when [[Tywin Lannister]] presents himself before King Joffrey.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Bear and the Maiden Fair]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

During the feast to celebrate the [[Marriage|wedding]] of Tyrion Lannister and [[Sansa Stark]], King Joffrey taunts Sansa by telling her that he may rape her, and have Ser [[Meryn Trant|Meryn]] and Ser Boros hold her as he does it.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Second Sons (episode)|Second Sons]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
Ser Jaime goes over the security plans for the Royal Wedding feast with Ser Meryn Trant, mentioning the place in which Ser Boros will be stationed&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Two Swords]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

After King Joffrey's [[Purple Wedding|assassination]], Cersei chastises Ser Jaime for posting only Ser Boros outside Tommen's door, and commands him to have four men guarding the future king day and night.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
